The urban-rural divide in chronic disease contributes to persistent geographic 
disparities in life expectancy in North Carolina. Policies and programs in 
resource-constrained rural areas should be designed to increase health equity 
and reduce this continuing divide by including greater community engagement and 
decision-making for meaningful, sustainable change.

